item.title: CVE-2017-6169|2024-09-17T01:51:56.273Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20pem
item.description: In versions 13.0.0, 12.0.0-12.1.3, or 11.6.0-11.6.2, an F5 BIG-IP virtual server using the URL categorization feature may cause the Traffic Management Microkernel (TMM) to produce a core file when it receives malformed URLs during categorization.
